name: Winnebago Industries, Inc.
description: Winnebago Industries, Inc. is a leading manufacturer of recreational vehicles (RVs) in North America, known for its iconic brand and commitment to innovation and quality. Founded in 1958, the company has a rich history of producing high-quality motorhomes, travel trailers, and fifth-wheel products that cater to the diverse needs of outdoor enthusiasts and travelers. Winnebago's product lineup features several popular models, including the Winnebago Vista, Forester, and Travato, which combine modern design with advanced technology and safety features. The company continues to evolve by incorporating sustainable practices and materials into its production process, emphasizing environmentally friendly manufacturing methods. With a focus on customer satisfaction, Winnebago aims to enhance the outdoor experience for its customers through a wide range of RV products and services. As the RV market continues to grow in popularity, Winnebago remains at the forefront of the industry, leveraging innovation and quality craftsmanship to meet the demands of the modern traveler.

faq.question: Who is the CEO of Winnebago Industries?
faq.answer: Michael Happe is the CEO of Winnebago Industries, Inc.

faq.question: Where is Winnebago headquartered?
faq.answer: Winnebago is headquartered in Forest City, Iowa, USA.

faq.question: What are some popular Winnebago models?
faq.answer: Popular Winnebago models include the Vista, Travato, and Forza.
